        %article#speakers
          %h2 Speakers

          %section.left
            %img{:src => 'images/speaker/drnic.png'}
            %p.title VP of Developer Evangelism at Engine Yard
            %p.name Dr Nic Williams
            %p
              Dr Nic is a developer’s developer. He writes blog posts for developers; creates tools, libraries and text editor extensions for developers; and speaks to developers at conferences.
            %p
              He’s the VP of Developer Evangelism at Engine Yard, the leading Platform as a Service. He has contributed to over 250 open source projects. He is known for creating or curating projects such as Rails Installer, Composite Primary Keys, Choc Top, App Scrolls, Rails TextMate bundle, New Gem, Tab Tab, GitHub Badges, Install Theme for Rails, and Dr Nic’s Magic Models.

          %br{:style => "clear: both"}

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/steveklabnik.png'}
            %p.name Steve Klabnik
            %p
              Ruby, anarchism, critical code studies. I love hypermedia APIs and teach awesome Ruby and Rails classes with Jumpstart Lab.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/josevalim.png'}
            %p.title Lead Developer at Plataformatec
            %p.name José Valim
            %p
              José Valim is a Rails Core member and author of Crafting Rails Applications. Also, he is the lead-developer of Plataformatec, a Ruby on Rails consultancy firm based in Brazil. He created and maintains many open source projects, the latest being Elixir and Dynamo, a language and web framework targeting the Erlang VM.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %p.name Charles Olivier Nutter
            %p
              Charles works on JRuby and other language implementations at Red Hat, helping to bring languages to the power of the JVM and bring the JVM to the broader polyglot world.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/brianford.png'}
            %p.name Brian Ford
            %p
              Brian has been working on Rubinius since December 2006 and with Engine Yard since January 2008. He created the RubySpec project to improve the standards for high quality, compliant Ruby implementations. He hopes to see Ruby become an even more widely used language and improved to make lives of developers even better. He also enjoys whisky but will accept a good wine in a pinch.

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/mitchellhashimoto.png'}
            %p.name Mitchell Hashimoto
            %p
              Mitchell is the creator of <a href="http://vagrantup.com">Vagrant</a>, an <a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/au/5373">O'Reilly author</a>, and a professional speaker. He is a well known and respected leader in the DevOps community, most commonly associated with building forward-thinking automation tools. He is also passionate about open source, and spends hours of his free time each day contributing to the community in any way possible.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/benjaminbrowning.png'}
            %p.title TorqueBox Lead at Red Hat
            %p.name Benjamin Browning
            %p
              Ben is the lead of the TorqueBox project and an active contributor to many other open-source projects. He spent several years in the enterprise Java world before embracing the JRuby goodness and now works hard to bring the Ruby and Java communities together through TorqueBox.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/piotrszotkowski.png'}
            %p.title Cheap Science Officer at Rebased
            %p.name Piotr Szotkowski
            %p
              Piotr Szotkowski is an assistant professor at Warsaw University of Technology (where he happily sneaks Ruby, EventMachine and newfangled database systems into the creaking world of twentieth-century academia) and a Ruby developer at <a href="http://rebased.pl">Rebased</a>. He’s also a long-time contributor to various open source projects for the civic sector and co-organiser of NetWtorek – monthly meetings of people from the NGO/non-profit and IT sectors, as well as SocHack – quarterly 48-hour hackatons for worthy causes, in coordination with <a href="http://www.rhok.org">Random Hacks of Kindness, <a href="http://www.opendataday.org">Open Data Day</a> and <a href="http://www.openeducationweek.org">Open Education Week</a>.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/andrzejkrzywda.png'}
            %p.name Andrzej Krzywda
            %p
              Ruby and Coffee programmer. The founder of Arkency and GameBoxed. Rails teacher at University of Wroclaw.
            %p
              He's originally a backend developer, with Rails experience since 2004. He knows all the pains and beauty of Rails. Now, after working for the last 2 years on frontends, he knows how to build them properly. He will teach us all the lessons he's learned and he's going to show a lot of production frontend code.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/karelminarik.png'}
            %p.title Ruby Developer
            %p.name Karel Minařík
            %p
              Karel Minařík is as a freelance designer and developer of web applications, consultant, software architect and Ruby/Rails and NoSQL evangelist. He lives in Prague with his wife and two daughters. Find out more at <a href="http://karmi.cz">http://karmi.cz</a>.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/honzakral.png'}
            %p.name Honza Král
            %p
              Honza is a Python programmer and Django core developer – since he is scared of the bright and shiny world of browsers, designers, and users he prefers to stay buried deep in the infrastructure code and just provides others with tools to do the actual site-building.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/arminronacher.png'}
            %p.title Software Engineer at Fireteam Ltd.
            %p.name Armin Ronacher
            %p
              Software developer and Open Source lover with a focus on Python. Author of Flask, Jinja2 and a few other Python projects. Interest in system architecture and API/graphical design and writing.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

